This paper deals with the segmentation of abdominal organs in CT images, which is a problem in medical image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a single-pass active learning method, which involves human quality assurance, to improve the segmentation performance. This method involves training a pre-existing model on augmented datasets, which is a common approach in machine learning. Therefore, the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of biomedical engineering. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.MED (Medical Imaging) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
